    "id" : 5,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 50.112, 173.942, 286.362, 512.148 ],
    "font" : "NimbusRomNo9L-ReguItal",
    "font size" : 10.909,
    "text color" : "[0.0]",
    "content" : "Irregular text is widely used. However, it is considerably difﬁcult to recognize because of its various shapes and distorted patterns. In this paper, we thus propose a multi-object rectiﬁed attention network (MORAN) for general scene text recognition. The MORAN consists of a multi-object rectiﬁcation network and an attention-based sequence recognition network. The multi-object rectiﬁcation network is designed for rectifying images that contain irregular text. It decreases the difﬁculty of recognition and enables the attention-based sequence recognition network to more easily read irregular text. It is trained in a weak supervision way, thus requiring only images and corresponding text labels. The attentionbased sequence recognition network focuses on target characters and sequentially outputs the predictions. Moreover, to improve the sensitivity of the attentionbased sequence recognition network, a fractional pickup method is proposed for an attention-based decoder in the training phase. With the rectiﬁcation mechanism, the MORAN can read both regular and irregular scene text. Extensive experiments on various benchmarks are conducted, which show that the MORAN achieves state-of-the-art performance. The source code is available1."
  }, {
