    "font" : "NimbusRomNo9L-Regu",
    "font size" : 10.909,
    "text color" : "[0.0]",
    "content" : "Scene text recognition is an essential process in computer vision tasks. Many practical applications such as trafﬁc sign reading, product recognition, intelligent inspection, and image searching, beneﬁt from the rich semantic information of scene text. With the development of scene text detection methods [11, 26, 46, 56], scene character recognition has emerged at the forefront of this research topic and is regarded as an open and very challenging research problem [45]."
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "pdfua_tag" : "P",
    "id" : 22,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 308.862, 105.211, 545.109, 199.651 ],
    "font" : "NimbusRomNo9L-Regu",
    "font size" : 10.909,
    "text color" : "[0.0]",
    "content" : "Nowadays, regular text recognition methods [3, 33, 41, 45, 50] have achieved notable success. Moreover, methods based on convolutional neural networks [3, 22, 50] have been broadly applied. Integrating recognition models with recurrent neural networks [17, 41, 42] and attention mechanisms [5, 6, 27, 51] yields better performance for these models."
  }, {
    "type" : "paragraph",
    "pdfua_tag" : "P",
    "id" : 23,
    "page number" : 1,
    "bounding box" : [ 308.862, 77.935, 545.109, 104.629 ],
    "font" : "NimbusRomNo9L-Regu",
    "font size" : 10.909,
    "text color" : "[0.0]",
    "content" : "Nevertheless, most current recognition models remain too unstable to handle multiple disturbances"
